Sentencas: This paper describes the effect of enhanced operating pressure on power density and efficiency of SOFC.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Experiments were carried out with planar anode-supported cells which were operated at 1073 K with an anode gas mixture of 30% H-2 and 70% N-2.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Pressure was varied between 1.35 and 8 bar.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Points of polarisation curves were measured at steady state with fuel utilisation varying from 30 to 50%.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Power density and efficiency of the fuel cell were analysed at different operating points.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results show that power density can be increased significantly (an increase up to 100% was measured) at constant efficiency.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An increase in efficiency in the range of 10% is achievable if power density is kept constant.
Titulo: Effect of pressure variation on power density and efficiency of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For all operating conditions, pressure effects show logarithmic behaviour.
